<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="22" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="22">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="22">Mature fruits were collected in June.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="22">
Vietnam (so far known only from Vu Quang National Park, Ha Tinh Province) (Figure 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Location of Vu Quang National Park (Black triangle), type locality of Lithocarpus vuquangensis." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.95.21832.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/182401" pageId="7" pageNumber="22">1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="7" pageNumber="22">The specific epithet is derived from its type locality, Vu Quang National Park.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
